== About Me
Hello and welcome to my page!
I'm coming from [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Athens Athens, Greece],
and I'm currently pursuing a PhD in [https://eecs.berkeley.edu/ EECS] with a designated emphasis in [https://www2.eecs.berkeley.edu/CCS/ Statistics]
at the [https://www.berkeley.edu/ UC Berkeley]. \n
I hold a MSc in [https://eecs.berkeley.edu/ EECS] from the [https://www.berkeley.edu/ UC Berkeley],
and a Diploma in [https://www.ece.ntua.gr/en ECE] from the [https://www.ntua.gr/en/ National Technical Univesity of Athens].

== Research
Broadly speaking my research interests lie in the areas of *probability*, *statistics*, *information theory*, *learning theory*, *stochastic control* and *optimization*.\n
In particularly I have researched topics about *concentration inequalities for Markov chains*, and *multi-armed bandit problems*.
